The Chairman of Air Peace Nigeria, Allen Onyema is presently at the House of Representatives to interact with the lawmakers on his role in providing free air flights to Nigerians in South Africa. He was supposed to be in the House on Tuesday, but the speaker had explained that he was unable to make it due to some reasons. Leader of the House, Ado Dogwa, this morning moved a motion that Chief Allen Onyema be admitted into the House, citing Order 19 rules 8 sub 2 of the standing rules of the House. Details still emerging… Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.